		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Hayamaru3000 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also if this is true would this mean for nsfs that are already ripped with the dmc channel sound, would the tune of the dmc change differently if raw pcm was supported? Is there a count listed for how many Nsf's with DMC/PCM samples have been ripped?</div>
<br />
<br />the only nsfs that support PCM samples are the demos posted at the beginning of this thread to my knowledge.  changing support for PCM will not change the sound of all the DMC-enabled NSFs out there.  it will merely more closely emulate what a NES can do.  games like Skate or Die 2 that used raw PCM will have to be re-ripped to actually hear the samples.

		

